76561198080006893,Recommended,302060,23608752,"Posted: 16 June, 2016",all,Mushroom,"Great, if HARD, sim game. If you want a challenge getting trailers around into some difficult parking places, then this is the game for you! I picked this up as part of the ET2 deluxe bundle, and have been enjoying playing it.Pros- variety of tasks.- able to choose several parking jobs if you get stuck (not limited to doing in exact order).- basic difficulty setting allows crashes to simply 'finish' level if you want to progress and come back later.- real sense of accomplishment when you do it right :)- decent physics engine.Cons- getting gold in all tasks is almost impossible (I've yet to get silver in all). If you NEED 100% achievements, you might find this one too hard.- some parking restraints are insane in pro.- in game radio turns off between levels, so generally more trouble that it's worth.- reversing mirrors don't work like ET2 (just go on popup mirror)Rating 7/10This game definitely wouldn't suit everyone, as the difficulty of all the tasks might end up on the high side. As an experienced ET2 player I started on pro, then quickly dropped the difficulty. Some parking locations seem just unfair (WHY would you park a trailer there??), but then the challenge can be quite satisfying. So if you want a game to test your backing skills, and pull some insane speeds to go for gold (or even silver), then definitely consider this game!"
